      <byline class="print_byline">By Todd Benson (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Benson, Todd</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Argentina's lower house of Congress approves fiscal responsibility bill, putting legislation one step from becoming law and meeting crucial demand to get fresh financing from International Monetary Fund (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Argentina's lower house of Congress passed a long-sought fiscal responsibility bill, putting the legislation one step from becoming law and meeting a crucial demand to get fresh financing from the International Monetary Fund. The bill, which was already approved by the Senate, must now be signed by President Néstor Kirchner to become law. The legislation conditions increases in federal and provincial spending to economic growth.</p>
        <p>Todd Benson (NYT)</p>
      </block>
